What does this program print?

```cpp
#include <iostream>

inline int doubled(int x) {
    return x * 2;
}

int main() {
    std::cout << doubled(5) << "\n";
    std::cout << doubled(0) << "\n";
    return 0;
}
```

A programmer wrote a small helper in a header and included it in two `.cpp` files. The project links cleanly when only one file includes the header, but fails with a linker error when both do. What is wrong?

```cpp
// helpers.h
#pragma once

int clamp(int v, int lo, int hi) {
    if (v < lo) return lo;
    if (v > hi) return hi;
    return v;
}
```

